The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Magma Shrachi net up 61% 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Magma Shrachi net up 61% 
          OUR BUREAU                                        Chamria: Upbeat    
	Calcutta, May 19: The net profit of Magma Shrachi Finance has increased 61 per cent to Rs 50.54 crore for the 2007-08 fiscal compared with Rs 31.40 crore in the previous year.        
	Magma Shrachi Finance vice-chairman and managing director Sanjay Chamria said revenues increased 69 per cent to Rs 471.43 crore during 2007-08 fiscal.        
	Chamria told reporters that the total asset base of the company stood at Rs 7,412.3 crore during the last fiscal, while disbursements increased 38 per cent to Rs 3,512.8 crore.        
	The company entered the tractor financing business last year through a joint venture with International Tractors Ltd.        
	Chamria said the company was currently financing 200 tractors per month.        
	Magma Shrachi had also entered into a preferred financer agreement with leading auto makers such as Maruti, Mahindra and Mahindra, Hyundai and General Motors.        
	Construction equipment segment had grown significantly during the year, with disbursements at Rs 952 crore, a rise of 74.9 per cent.                                                                                                                                     
